1. Installing the badwords.pl command

To use the badwords merge command, you must first download the script badwords.pl and place it in the correct DXSpider directory.

1.1. Create the destination directory (if it does not exist)

In your DXSpider system, commands are stored under local_cmd.
If the load directory does not exist, create it:

mkdir -p /spider/local_cmd/load

(Adjust /spider if your DXSpider installation uses a different base path)

1.2. Download the script using wget

Run the following command to download the script directly from GitHub:

wget -O /spider/local_cmd/load/badwords.pl \
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/main/load/badwords.pl

This will download the correct file and save it with the proper name.


2. Add into your crontab

# badip
30 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN https://github.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/blob/main/download/badip.torexit')
30 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN https://github.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/blob/main/download/badip.torrelay')
30 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN https://github.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/blob/main/download/badip.global')
32 * * * * run_cmd('load/badip')

# baddx, badspotter, badnode, badword
33 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN https://raw.githubusercontent.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/main/download/baddx')
33 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN https://raw.githubusercontent.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/main/download/badspotter')
33 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN https://raw.githubusercontent.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/main/download/badnode')
33 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN https://raw.githubusercontent.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/main/download/badword.new')
35 * * * * run_cmd('load/badwords')
